<Issue id="18627" key="FABC-472" number="472" project="10607" reporter="smithbk" assignee="skarim" creator="smithbk" type="10001" summary="Add a TLS profile to the default config file for fabric-ca-server" priority="3" resolution="10000" status="6" created="2017-06-23 20:03:58.0" updated="2018-07-20 19:16:06.0" resolutiondate="2017-08-11 07:32:09.0" votes="0" watches="2" workflowId="32654" security="10001"> <description><! CDATA In order to make issuance of TLS certs with the appropriate usage, add a tls profile to the default config as follows: {code} tls: usage: - server auth - client auth expiry: 8760h {code}  This causes the server to issue certificates targeted for this profile with the following usage (as printed by openssl) which is common for TLS certificates. {code} X509v3 Extended Key Usage:  TLS Web Server Authentication, TLS Web Client Authentication {code}  In order to target the tls profile, use the "--enrollment.profile tls" option as follows: {code} # fabric-ca-client enroll --enrollment.profile tls -u http://<enrollmentID>:<secret>@localhost:7054 {code}   ></description> </Issue>
